data.title: EastEnders Season 16
data.meta_description: The everyday lives of working-class residents of Albert Square, a traditional Victorian square of terrace houses surrounding a park in the East End of London's Walford borough.
data.text:
Ian clings to a lost hope, and Irene gets advice to clear the air with Terry. Beppe wonders why Sandra has returned to his life. Steve continues lurking but Jackie is determined to make him face the Square. Jamie is devastated by Janine's alarming gossip.

Steve is humiliated when he finally ventures forth but has the final word. Irene tries to talk to Terry and Mel agrees to meet with Ian to set him straight. Kathy discover her son's lie and heads for the airport once again. Passion is in the air for Ricky.

Tensions between Lisa and Mark escalate when he refuses to see a doctor. Rumours concerning Matthew's return worry a nervous Steve and Beppe worries about a stalker. A letter from Wicksy distresses Pat and Irene comes into some money.

Mark's life hangs by a thread as the family gathers round him at the hospital. Ian sinks to new lows in his quest for revenge and Rosa is crestfallen when events force Beppe and Sandra closer together. Irene's windfall elates Terry but, elsewhere, Steve is distressed.

Rosa faces her worst fears as Sandra tightens her grip on Beppe and decides to take actions. Steve is terrified that he is being stalked. Pauline despairs and Lisa is distraught when they have words at Mark's bedside.

Terry has a change of plans which Roy rebuffs. Now he has to come clean to Irene. Meanwhile, Dan has a lock-in at the Queen Vic while Janine has a party that soon gets out of control. The di Marco family remember Guiseppe and Steve gets another shock.

Terry's charms work on Irene when he comes up with a surprises anniversary present. Sandra takes desperate measures to spend time with her son. Lisa is faced with a tough decision and Phil is no help. Steve takes extreme measures for self-protection and Kim turns to Fred for advice. Teams for the Vic Vs. Giuseppe's snooker match are decided.

A police visit to the car lot gives Roy food for thought over a business deal. Melanie, Natalie, Jackie and Lisa have a girls night out but Lisa's mind is elsewhere and Ian is back in business with uniform staff.

Lisa tests the waters with Phil about a new addition to his family. Ricky has a taste of revenge by tossing a spanner in the works when Dan plans some after-hours drinking to send Fred off in style.

Roy cannot bring himself to tell Pat the truth and Terry is desperate to find someone to look after the shop while he takes Irene away. Lisa is thrilled when Phil asks her to move in with him until she makes a startling discovery.

The Vic is locked in due to unexploded bomb. Frank and Peggy announce their plans to move to Portugal. Phil continues his fight with Billy. Lisa tells Phil it's all over. Lisa reveals why Melanie left Ian after their wedding.

Steve hides his drug problem from Beppe but Billy is on to him. Phil refuses to let Roy back out of their deal as he tries desperately to sell the dodgy cars. Ian discovers Laura's secret and Peggy's suspicions about Lisa run rampant.

Natalie decides that the dating agency has had its day and Barry tries to lift her spirits with a brilliant idea to save money.

When Roy receives bad news from his pension company he worries about his future but Phil has a proposition for him.

Ian's bank manager comes to dinner to discuss a loan but the evening goes anything but smoothly.

Sonia is devastated to learn that Enrico has another girlfriend and turns to a close friend for comfort but gets a bit more than expected!

Roy finds a dodgy deal appealing.

Mark invites Lisa to share and Phil loses his temper when he receives some unwelcome advice from a drunken Melanie.

Tensions mount at e20 and Janine's suspicions are confirmed.

Beppe and Sandra grow closer, much to Rosa's horror. Janine's detective work around the car lot becomes too much for Roy.

And Lisa decides to sell her beloved bike.

Rosa decides to take action and makes Sandra an offer. Peggy celebrates her birthday and Janine begins her new job at the Vic.

Lisa finds the cat is out of the bag.

Roy is in for a trying time when Laura sets Ian's heart on a new car. Terry is having trouble recapturing his lost youth.

Phil tells Peggy a few home truths and she responds with one of her own. Mel finds concern over Steve's health.

Phil is determined to win Lisa over, but he could be too late. Phil warns Roy he was in much too deep to stop selling the stolen cars.

Janine lets out Roy's secret when he refuses her demands.

After arguing with Irene, Terry pours his heart out to Melanie but tries to take their friendship one step too far.

Beppe is concerned about Sandra's disappearance and Rosa confesses her secret to Irene.

Gianni is angry with Jackie until she explains the reasons for her behaviour.

Dan starts to feel the heat in the Vic, but discovers some useful information from Janine. Ricky is reeling from his recent trip. Beppe furious at his mother's behaviour, confronts Rosa about the cheque.

Peggy goes to the hospital to discuss her surgery and Billy plays games with Steve.

Things go from bad to worse for Ricky, with disastrous consequences for all.

Roy finds his dodgy stock down a few cars and Melanie wins free fish and chips at Ian's in the prize draw.

Miserable Ricky heads East in an emotional two-hander with Phil.

After losing his wife, son, and finally his marbles Ricky says an emotional farewell to the Square.

There is a shock in store for Mel when she attempts to make amends with Dan. Gianni is left reeling after feeling the full force of Jackie's wrath.

Furious at Dan, Phil takes his mood out on Lisa but Peggy may have the final solution to their problems.

Phil and Roy are amazed by Peggy's plan to get rid of Dan once and for all after a police visit gives her an idea.

Lisa has warning pains and Jamie delivers a warning to Janine.

Phil and Lisa have to deal with some shocking news. Mel and Dan are forced to confront their feelings for each other.
